es.',1977,4.29,1072,7584),(257,'De Profundis and Other Writings','','Oscar Wilde','Fiction','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ANYo1XCPqt4C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','No Marketing Blurb',1973,4.21,252,2253),(258,'Redburn','','Herman Melville','Fiction','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=LH87V-JOBSEC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','The hardships of life at sea and the realities of distant cities provide young Redburn with a startling introduction to the world',1976,3.61,448,522),(259,'The Pursuit of the Well-beloved and the Well-beloved','','Thomas Hardy','Fiction','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=tLjGScN9eNAC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','Hardy\'s two versions of a strange story set in the weird landscape of Portland. The central figure is a man obsessed both with the search for his ideal woman and with sculpting the perfect figure of Aphrodite.',2007,3.59,416,120),(260,'Ivanhoe','','Walter Scott','Fiction','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=IiOgdjKRM5oC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','Scott\'s classic historical romance, set in the twelfth-century England of Richard I, depicts the adventures of the heroic Wilfred of Ivanhoe in winning the hand of beautiful Lady Rowena.',2000,3.75,544,72038),(261,'Maggie, a Girl of the Streets, and Other Tales of New York','','Stephen Crane','Fiction','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=TeOwd7KTsxgC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','Portrays the brutal effects of the poverty and loneliness of slum life.',2000,3.66,272,2405),(262,'The Canterbury Tales','','Geoffrey Chaucer','Poetry','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ab8tos14Ti0C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','A retelling of the medieval poem about a group of travelers on a pilgrimage to Canterbury and the tales they tell each other',1977,3.49,489,1024),(263,'The Comedy of Dante Alighieri, the Florentine: Purgatory','','Dante Alighieri','Poetry','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=sQb_yAEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','The most celebrated work of Dante is the Divine comedy--a vision of hell, purgatory and heaven that provides a strangely surrealistic view of medieval attitudes on religious dogma and the price of disobedience.',1949,4.02,388,341),(264,'Faust','','Johann Goethe','Drama','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=IYSxmzIyouoC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','A brief analysis of the development, style, and protagonists of the play is included with Goethe\'s masterpiece about a troubled man who sells his soul to the devil.',1959,3.73,288,120),(265,'Home of the Gentry','','Ivan Turgenev','Fiction','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=j7snw8iJobgC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','The nobleman Lavretsky, broken and disillusioned by a failed marriage, returns from Paris to his Russian estate, where he begins to fall in love with a young woman named Liza.',1970,3.92,298,2070),(266,'Notes from Underground','The Double','Fyodor Dostoyevsky','Fiction','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=-s47DK9xBS4C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','A single, tormented, character dominates both of these short novels written at different stages of Dostoyevsky\'s career',1972,4.2,287,4537),(267,'Li Po and Tu Fu','','Arthur R. V. Cooper','Poetry','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=S4SPUkPIIZYC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','Offers translations of poems by the two Chinese writers.',1973,4.11,256,359);
